<item>
            <title>[LU-19612] IPv6 - Remote dir creation on other MDTs fails</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19612</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre clients mounting with network restrictions (network=tcp or network=tcp6), only the first MDT (MDT0000) becomes accessible. All additional MDTs (MDT0001+) fail to connect, causing remote directory creation commands&#160;to fail with &lt;b&gt;&quot;No such device&quot;&lt;/b&gt; error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug occurs when a Lustre client mounts a multi-MDT filesystem using &lt;b&gt;explicit network-type NIDs&lt;/b&gt;  in a mixed IPv4/IPv6 environment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="93691">LU-19612</key>
            <summary>IPv6 - Remote dir creation on other MDTs fails</summary>
