                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="483717" author="JIRAUSER19234" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2026 22:06:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cannot reproduce on current version of Lustre&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="479114" author="JIRAUSER19234" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2025 03:58:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tappro&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tappro&quot;&gt;tappro&lt;/a&gt;&#160;I assumed that specifying @tcp6 NIDs in the mount command&#160;would automatically set a network restriction equivalent to -o network=tcp6. However, after looking again I see that doesn&apos;t happen as I had thought.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="479089" author="tappro" created="Fri, 21 Nov 2025 21:34:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mdilger&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mdilger&quot;&gt;mdilger&lt;/a&gt; , I don&apos;t see in EX-12890 that &lt;tt&gt;&apos;-o network&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; option is used there in mount command on client side. How did you find out it causes problems? Did I miss something or maybe that is not correct ticket linked?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="479077" author="JIRAUSER19234" created="Fri, 21 Nov 2025 18:26:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tappro&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tappro&quot;&gt;tappro&lt;/a&gt; are able to advise on EX-12890? Perhaps I have misunderstood their ticket and its just a config error.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="479040" author="tappro" created="Fri, 21 Nov 2025 11:16:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is a bug, if client uses explicit network type then it is expected it is able to reach all servers via that network type, if it can&apos;t then explicit network type should not be used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution provided in patch would just break network isolation and multi-tenancy feature, because client becomes able to access all networks MGS knows about&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="479013" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 21 Nov 2025 07:28:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Maximilian Dilger &amp;lt;mdilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62649&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62649&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
